Security was reinforced around the Federal High Court sitting in Yenagoa, Bayelsa State on Friday to avert a repeat of the Thursday afternoon invasion of the court by armed hoodlums. The hoodlums numbering twenty overpowered the security men on duty and forced their way into Court II which was handling a pre-election suit involving the candidates of the All Progressive Congress, APC, and Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, for the Bayelsa Central Senatorial District and destroyed the valuables of judicial officers and court properties. <img class=" wp-image-1503643 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?resize=599%2C449&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="599" height="449" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?resize=58%2C44&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?resize=260%2C194&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?resize=173%2C130&amp;ssl=1 173w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.28.00-PM.jpeg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w" sizes="(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The marauding hoodlums manhandled and chased away lawyers and staff at the court and made away with mobile phones, cash and other valuables. A court official told Vanguard reporter that dynamite was also thrown into the court premises but was promptly disabled by the police anti-bomb squad before it could explode. <img class=" wp-image-1503642 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-04-at-5.27.57-PM.jp